snippet: Two years after President Hosni Mubarak fell, Egyptian street activists like Mohamed Mokbel say they are still fighting for the democratic goals of the Arab Spring revolt.
abstract: Egyptian street activists like Mohamed Mokbel, two years after ouster of Pres Hosni Mubarak, say they are still fighting for democracy amid disappointment in Egypt’s new Islamist leaders; many have turned against Pres Mohamed Morsi and his Muslim Brotherhood allies because they believe he has sided with abusive and unaccountable security forces.
lead_paragraph: Two years after President Hosni Mubarak fell, Egyptian street activists like Mohamed Mokbel say they are still fighting for the democratic goals of the Arab Spring revolt.

headline.seo: Many Egyptians Fight on Streets to Restore Revolution’s Goals
